0e21179a-f1a5-4215-9ce9-b54344087e25.26631de9-9936-4f97-b0c5-15d1e38849b6.description=
Getting file system list, and free space quantities.
WMI query does not work in Windows 2000, Windows NT 4.0, and Windows Me/98/95.

Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. 0e21179a-f1a5-4215-9ce9-b54344087e25.description=
Calculates the average usage across all disks in a host.
WMI query does not work in Windows 2000, Windows NT 4.0, and Windows Me/98/95.

Inputs\:
host - the host to measure disk usage on.
username - username for host.
password - password for username.

Responses\:
success - the operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.

Returns\:
the average disk usage.

flow.name: Get Average Disk Usage

staticBinding.value: Select Name, FreeSpace, Size, VolumeDirty from Win32_LogicalDisk where DriveType = 3
